com.brightcove.auth.ap.delegates

Class AccessEnablerCallbackDelegate

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.brightcove.auth.ap.delegates.AccessEnablerCallbackDelegate
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.adobe.adobepass.accessenabler.api.IAccessEnablerDelegate
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AdobePassDelegate

    public class AccessEnablerCallbackDelegate
extends java.lang.Object
implements com.adobe.adobepass.accessenabler.api.IAccessEnablerDelegate
    Manages all the callbacks from the underlying Adobe Pass library and emits events back to the UI thread by using the EventEmitter

    It cannot be instantiate by itself, but must be subclassed first

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Maximilian Nyman (max.nyman@anvilcreative.com)
    See Also:
    AdobePassDelegate, IAccessEnablerDelegate, EventEmitter.on(String, com.brightcove.player.event.EventListener)
